1. The target user is a young person who want to stay on the bleeding edge of pop culture.
2. Get the most current and in depth information about pop culture
3. I don’t know if the visual hierarchy lends itself to accomplishing that goal. I have a hard time telling what is an add and what isn’t, so I don’t want to click on anything.
4. Everything is sans source pro
5. All of the text is very readable and the font fits the via of the page
6. Line spacing is colors and weights seem appropriate 
7. The biggest thing above the fold is an advert. Opposing the style of NYTimes TMZ has chosen to put one story across the entire screen as you scroll. This results in a ton of scrolling. The layout should be more condensed. 
